---
title: Cheesy Black Bean Tacos with Poblano & Smoky Red Pepper Crema
description: Don’t get us wrong, we’re always up for going out for tacos, but we absolutely love making them at home. That way, we can customize them to fit our EXACT craving of the moment. For this vegetarian version, we ditch the meat for a hearty filling of poblano and spiced black beans, then top smoky red pepper crema and not one, but TWO kinds of cheese for maximum melt-factor. Oh, and did we mention these are ready in just 15 minutes? That’s faster than waiting in line at our local taco spot.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/cheesy-black-bean-tacos-20229c78.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/cheesy-black-bean-tacos-6092a29805cbea6ace32da37-6c9d63f5.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 850 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 95 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 32 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 2380 mg
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Mexican
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cheesy-black-bean-tacos-6092a29805cbea6ace32da37
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, core, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1} crosswise into strips.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If needed, add a splash of water to help poblano soften.

While poblano cooks, drain and rinse @black beans{13.4%ounce}.

Once poblano is softened, stir in scallion whites and @southwest spice blend{2%teaspoons}.

> Be sure to measure the Southwest Spice—we sent more.

Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add beans, @Tex-Mex paste{1}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring, until filling is combined and thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Sprinkle black bean filling with @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Cover pan until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with black bean filling, @smoky red pepper crema{2%tablespoons}, and scallion greens. Serve.